54.1	Nutraceutical	Nutraceutical	The Indians, Egyptians, Chinese, and Sumerians are just a few civilizations that have provided evidence suggesting that foods can be effectively used as medicine to treat and prevent disease. Ayurveda,the 5,000 year old ancient Indian health science, have mentioned benefits of food for therapautic purpose. Documents hint that the medicinal benefits of food have been explored for thousands of years. Hippocrates, considered by some to be the father of Western medicine, said that people should “Let food be thy medicine.”	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Hippocrates_rubens.jpg/170px-Hippocrates_rubens.jpg
